# 🚦 Traffic Light Control using Deep Reinforcement Learning

## Overview
This project implements an intelligent traffic light control system using Deep Q-Networks (DQN) to optimize traffic flow at a single intersection. The RL agent learns to dynamically adjust traffic light phases based on real-time traffic conditions.

## Key Features
- Custom OpenAI Gym environment for traffic simulation
- DQN agent with experience replay and target networks
- Real-time visualization of traffic states
- Comprehensive evaluation metrics
- Comparison with fixed-time controller
- Configurable parameters via YAML

## Architecture
- **Environment**: 4-lane intersection with vehicle queues
- **State Space**: Queue lengths, waiting times, current phase
- **Action Space**: NS green or EW green
- **Reward**: Negative of total waiting time
- **Agent**: DQN with 3 hidden layers (64-64-32)

## Results
The RL agent achieves:
- 30-40% reduction in average waiting time
- Improved throughput compared to fixed-time control
- Adaptive response to varying traffic patterns

